## 3. Monitoring and alerting matrix (Monitoring & Alerts)

Define the core metrics that must be covered end-to-end across the system.

| Monitoring dimension | Toolchain | Alert threshold (P0/P1) | Responder / group |
|---------|--------|----------------|------------|
| Business gateway | APISIX / Nginx | 5xx error rate > 1% / P99 latency > 500ms | Dev on-call + SRE |
| Database layer | RDS Dashboards | Spike in slow SQL count / CPU > 80% / disk > 85% | DBA / SRE |
| Host / Pod | Prometheus + Grafana | Node CPU > 90% / memory OOM alert | SRE |
| Business logs | ELK / Loki | Keyword matches for `Exception`, `FATAL` exceed threshold | Dev on-call |

## 4. Disaster recovery and contingency plans (Disaster Recovery)

- **Data backup strategy**: `[e.g., RDS daily full cold backup, incremental Binlog real-time archive. S3 data enables cross-AZ replication.]`
- **AZ disaster recovery strategy**: `[e.g., core services must be deployed in at least 2 AZs (Availability Zones), with automatic traffic failover when an AZ goes down.]`
- **Degradation plan**: `[e.g., during network-wide traffic peaks for big promotions, support one-click degradation of non-critical "comment system" and "recommendation feed".]`

